headline: How Recent Developments Are Rewriting the Story for Netflix
summary: Netflix’s consensus analyst price target has been sharply reduced from nearly $1,350 to around $135 per share. This reflects significant model revisions after recent business developments. This adjustment comes as Wall Street analysts weigh evolving expectations for the company’s ongoing business momentum and shifting risk profile. Read on to find out how investors can stay attuned to these important narrative changes as they unfold. Analyst Price Targets don't always capture the full story...

headline: Taylor Swift Movie Helped AMC Capture More Than One-Third Of Theater Market Share. 'Thank You, Taylor'
summary: Taylor Swift's promotional film "Taylor Swift: The Official Release Party of a Showgirl," a behind-the-scenes film of the singer's 12th studio album, helped AMC Theaters (NYSE:AMC) capture 36% of the domestic movie theater market share in one weekend, AMC CEO Adam Aron said during the company's recent Q3 earnings call.
